2, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1645, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5508519141507472, \"rank\": 0.7129793321850184, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PICTURE\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1536}, {\"ngram\": \"Sportsfile Reporter\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"Reporter\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"Jul\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"The 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the corner\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"an 'elaborate' and 'unprecedented' security operation\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowds\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 25,000 Irish fans expected to travel to the city, and as a result, Irish garda\\u00ed will be among the forces deployed to ensure the safety of both participants and spectators.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1767, \"end\": 1772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999762426345, \"rank\": 1.4884016152449929e-08, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999762426345, \"rank\": 1.4884016152449929e-08, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1808}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"the forces\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1894}, {\"ngram\": \"both participants\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The security measures in Paris are extensive, including an anti-terrorism border along the River Seine, extending 6 kilometers on both sides.\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.03327160788861e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The security measures\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1954}, {\"ngram\": \"an anti-terrorism border\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2013}, {\"ngram\": \"6 kilometers\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"both sides\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2073}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scene is one of 'high' security: about six roads converging at a major junction will see three blocked off by metal barriers.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scene\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"'high' security\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"about six roads\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"a major junction\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"metal barriers\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, dozens of police officers are to be standing at roadblocks and checking QR codes to verify locals' addresses and conducting thorough checks of their bags before admission.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"police officers\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2241}, {\"ngram\": \"roadblocks\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"QR codes\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2296}, {\"ngram\": \"locals' addresses\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"thorough checks\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"their bags\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2369}, {\"ngram\": \"admission\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony, which will take place along the Seine rather than inside a stadium, will see a no-fly zone extending 150 kilometers above the ceremony site while snipers will be deployed on rooftops to maintain surveillance and ensure safety.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2443, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 9.101044528284765e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2432}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"a no-fly zone\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony site\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"snipers\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"rooftops\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"surveillance\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"safety\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9's Kate Varley, reporting from Paris, said: \\\"It's safe to say that rarely in peacetime has the French capital experienced such high levels of security.\\\"\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.